&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The first general elections to the Lok Sabha were held in India -&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Between 25&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;October 1951 and 21&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;February 1952.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The right to vote&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is a &lt;strong&gt;legal right.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Election Commission of India (ECI)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is a constitutional body vested with powers to supervise, direct and control the election process of the country.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Election Commission of India (EC) came into force on&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;25 January 1950&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;From 2011, this day is observed as&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lsquo;National Voters&amp;rsquo; Day&amp;rsquo;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Election Commission functions as a multi-member body comprising of&lt;strong&gt; 3 commissioners.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Chief and the two other Election Commissioners&lt;/strong&gt; have the same powers and emoluments including salaries, which are the same as a Supreme Court judge.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The tenure&amp;nbsp;of Election Commissioners is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;6 years or until they attain 65 years&lt;/strong&gt;, whichever happens first. They can also be removed or can resign at any time before the expiry of their term.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Election Commissioners are&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;appointed by the President.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 324&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the Indian&amp;nbsp;Constitution deals it the power and authority to conduct, control, and supervise the entire election process in the country including elections to the Parliament, the Legislatures of every state, and to the offices of the President and Vice-President.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Election Commission is an all-India body that is common to&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;both the Central government and the State governments.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Commission&amp;rsquo;s functions and powers with respect to elections to the offices of the President, the Vice President, the state legislators, and the Parliament are divided under three headings:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Administrative Powers, Advisory Powers, and Quasi-Judicial Powers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;16 October 1989,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the voting age was reduced from 21 to 18 years by the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;61&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;Constitutional Amendment Act 1988.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It must be noted here that the commission does not deal with the elections to the Municipalities and Panchayats in the states. Hence, a separate State Election Commission is provided by the Constitution of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Election Commission of India (ECI) came into force on&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;25 January 1950&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp;From 2011, this day is observed as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;National Voters&amp;rsquo; Day&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 326&lt;/strong&gt; deals with the Universal adult franchise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;img height=&quot;55px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage13.png&quot; width=&quot;180px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: square;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Headquarters of&amp;nbsp;Election Commission of India -&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Nirvachan Sadan, New Delhi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The current&amp;nbsp;Chief&amp;nbsp;Election Commissioner of India&amp;nbsp;- &lt;strong&gt;Sushil Chandra.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The first Chief&amp;nbsp;Election Commissioner of India&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Sukumar Sen.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The longest-serving&amp;nbsp;Chief&amp;nbsp;Election Commissioner of India&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;K. V. K. Sundaram.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The shortest-serving&amp;nbsp;Chief&amp;nbsp;Election Commissioner of India&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;V. S. Ramadevi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The first woman to become the Chief Election Commissioner of India -&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;V. S. Ramadevi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Prime Minister who&amp;nbsp;reduced the voting age from 21 to 18 years -&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Rajiv Gandhi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;<br><br>&lt;p&gt;सही उत्तर &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;दल&amp;nbsp;का नामांकन&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; है।&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;दल का नामांकन पार्टी का टिकट है।&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;दल के नामांकन को अक्सर पार्टी टिकट कहा जाता है।&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;एक पार्टी टिकट एक &lt;strong&gt;विशेष राजनीतिक दल द्वारा चुनाव में भाग लेने के लिए एक विशेष उम्मीदवार को दिया जाने वाला भत्ता है।&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;पार्टी कुछ ऐसे &lt;strong&gt;उम्मीदवारों का चयन करती है जो अपने निर्वाचन क्षेत्र में मजबूत होते हैं और जिनके पास अपने निर्वाचन क्षेत्र में जीतने की अधिक क्षमता होती है।&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ऐसे व्यक्तियों को चुनाव लड़ने के लिए सदस्य घोषित किया जाता है और उन्हें पार्टी का टिकट दिया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;भारत में सात राष्ट्रीय दल हैं।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

